au.gov.naa.digipres.xena.kernel.metadatawrapper
Class MetaDataWrapperManager

java.lang.Object
  au.gov.naa.digipres.xena.kernel.metadatawrapper.MetaDataWrapperManager

public class MetaDataWrapperManager
extends java.lang.Object

Manager for XMLFilter instances. These are primarily used to wrap normalised objects with meta-data. We also have unwrap filters which can strip off the meta-data. These wrappers and unwrappers form pairs.

See Also:
XMLFilter

addMetaDataWrappers

public void addMetaDataWrappers(java.util.Map<AbstractMetaDataWrapper,org.xml.sax.XMLFilter> wrapperMap)
Add the wrapper and unwrapper pairs to the Meta Data Wrapper Manager. Given that the first wrapper loaded will become the default wrapper, iteration order could be important. In this case, use a LinkedHashMap to ensure entries are iterated in the order they were put into the map.
